======================================================================
LEE-YANG ZEROS FOR PALEY TOURNAMENTS
======================================================================

Connection: H(T) = I(Omega(T), 2) [OCF]
Lee-Yang zeros = roots of I(Omega(T), x)
Theorem (Chudnovsky-Seymour): claw-free G => all roots real negative
Our result: T_p claw-free for p<=8, fails p=9 (first case n=11 is T_11)


